spec: socket_extra111
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(socket)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html — Python socket module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/socket.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/socketmodule.c"
    - "socket_extra110.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket __enter__ and __exit__ context manager methods (Python function type, qualnames, co_argcount) / socket.__repr__ qualname and type / socket.socket.__module__/__qualname__ equality and lengths / socket.socket.fileno as method_descriptor (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra109.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket Python-defined method co_argcount values — close, makefile, accept, detach (all have __code__); socket.socket.__init__ co_argcount; method qualnames for close/makefile/accept/detach/__init__; type names for Python-level socket methods (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra108.zspec.zsdl — covers gethostname/gethostbyname/getnameinfo C-level identity / getaddrinfo/getfqdn Python-level identity / setdefaulttimeout/getdefaulttimeout C-level / create_connection Python-level / getfqdn code attributes (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra107.zspec.zsdl — covers socket SO_* option constants class names and integer values / socket.error and socket.timeout class identity and MRO (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra106.zspec.zsdl — covers IPPROTO_TCP/UDP/IP/ICMP/IPV6 class names and values / SOL_SOCKET class name and value (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra105.zspec.zsdl — covers AF_*/SOCK_* class module/qualname/mro / AddressFamily/SocketKind name/module/metaclass/base identity (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra104.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket C-method types / socket.socket method qualname lengths / socket.socket Python-level method types and class identity (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra103.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.inet_aton/ntoa/pton/ntop class names and qualname lengths / htons/htonl/ntohs/ntohl class names / herror/gaierror MRO depth / AddressFamily/SocketKind MRO depth (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra102.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket __qualname__/__name__.__len__()==6 / error/__name__.__eq__('OSError') / herror/gaierror qualname/module/bases / AddressFamily/SocketKind qualname lengths and module (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra99.zspec.zsdl — covers socket module-level function qualname lengths / SocketIO class metaclass/module/bases (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra96.zspec.zsdl — covers AF_INET/AF_UNIX/AF_INET6/AF_UNSPEC and SOCK_STREAM/SOCK_DGRAM/SOCK_RAW class names / AddressFamily/SocketKind __bases__ (table + invariants)."
  notes:
    - "This spec extends socket through socket_extra110; it does NOT duplicate invariants present in those files."
    - "Wave 271 theme: socket module-level dunder attributes — __name__, __package__, __spec__ — and the socket.__all__ list; __name__=='socket' (6 chars); __package__=='' (empty string, len 0); __spec__ is a ModuleSpec named 'socket'; __spec__.has_location==True; __all__ has 238 elements; loader is SourceFileLoader; __package__.__eq__('')==True."
    - "socket.__name__ == 'socket'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__package__ == '' (empty string). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "type(socket.__name__).__name__ == 'str'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__spec__.__class__.__name__ == 'ModuleSpec'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__spec__.name == 'socket'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__spec__.has_location == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "len(socket.__name__) == 6. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "len(socket.__package__) == 0. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "len(socket.__all__) == 238. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__all__[0] == 'fromfd'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__all__[-1] == 'recv_fds'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__loader__.__class__.__name__ == 'SourceFileLoader'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "type(socket.__spec__.origin).__name__ == 'str'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__package__.__eq__('') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.__name__.__eq__('socket') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: socket.__all__ has 238 elements — far more than hashlib.__all__ (19 elements) because socket exports constants (AF_*, SOCK_*, IPPROTO_*, SO_*, IP_*, TCP_*, etc.) in addition to functions and classes. The first element is 'fromfd' and the last is 'recv_fds'. socket.__package__ is '' (empty string, len 0); socket is a top-level module not a subpackage."
    - "Note: socket is a hybrid module — socket.py is the Python-level wrapper (SourceFileLoader) around _socket (C extension). The module __name__ is 'socket' and the class inside is also named 'socket' (socket.socket). socket.__spec__.has_location is True (loaded from socket.py). socket.__loader__ is SourceFileLoader. This parallels hashlib which also wraps _hashlib with a .py layer."
    - "Note: socket_extra110 anchors socket.socket class module/qualname equality; socket_extra102 anchors socket.socket.__qualname__.__len__()==6. This spec anchors the socket MODULE-level __name__, __package__, __spec__, __all__ attributes for the first time (distinct from socket.socket CLASS attributes)."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.__name__.__eq__('socket')
# socket.__package__.__eq__('')
# type(socket.__name__).__name__.__eq__('str')
# len(socket.__name__) == 6
# len(socket.__package__) == 0
#
# Wave 271 theme: socket module __name__ and __package__ equality and lengths.
#
# socket.__name__ is 'socket' (6 chars). socket.__package__ is '' (empty string,
# length 0) because socket is a top-level module, not a subpackage. The socket
# module name (6 chars) is shorter than 'hashlib' (7 chars) and longer than
# 'uuid' (4 chars). type(socket.__name__).__name__ is 'str'. Note: socket.__name__
# refers to the MODULE attribute, not to socket.socket.__qualname__ (which is
# also 'socket' — but that is the class attribute). socket_extra110 anchors
# socket.socket class module/qualname; this spec anchors the module-level attrs.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table socket_extra111.socket_module_name_and_package_equality_and_lengths:
  description: "socket.__name__.__eq__('socket')==True / socket.__package__.__eq__('')==True / type(socket.__name__).__name__.__eq__('str')==True / socket.__name__.__len__()==6 / socket.__package__.__len__()==0 — module __name__=='socket' (6 chars; shorter than hashlib=7, longer than uuid=4); __package__=='' (empty string, len 0; top-level module); type of __name__ is str; MODULE-level attrs (distinct from socket.socket CLASS attrs); extra110 anchors class attrs; first sockmeta111 anchor"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: module_identity
  id_prefix: sockmeta111

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [name_eq,       "socket.__name__.__eq__",                    ["socket"], true, "socket.__name__ is 'socket' (6 chars; module name as registered in sys.modules; the socket MODULE, not socket class)"]
    - [package_eq,    "socket.__package__.__eq__",                 [""],       true, "socket.__package__ is '' (empty string; top-level module; not a subpackage of any package)"]
    - [name_type_str, "socket.__name__.__class__.__name__.__eq__", ["str"],    true, "type(socket.__name__) is 'str' (module __name__ is always a string; the registered module name)"]
    - [name_len,      "socket.__name__.__len__",                   [],         6,    "socket.__name__.__len__() is 6 ('socket': 6 chars; s-o-c-k-e-t)"]
    - [package_len,   "socket.__package__.__len__",                [],         0,    "socket.__package__.__len__() is 0 (empty string; top-level modules have __package__=='' not None)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.__spec__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('ModuleSpec')
# socket.__spec__.name.__eq__('socket')
# socket.__spec__.has_location == True
# socket.__loader__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('SourceFileLoader')
# type(socket.__spec__.origin).__name__.__eq__('str')
#
# Wave 271 theme: socket module __spec__ attributes and loader type.
#
# socket.__spec__ is a ModuleSpec with name 'socket' and has_location True.
# The loader is SourceFileLoader — socket is implemented as socket.py (Python
# source) wrapping the _socket C extension. The origin is a str (path to
# socket.py). This parallels hashlib (also SourceFileLoader wrapping _hashlib).
# socket.__spec__ has_location True confirms socket is loaded from disk, not
# frozen. No prior socket spec anchors socket MODULE-level __spec__ attributes.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table socket_extra111.socket_module_spec_loader_origin_attributes:
  description: "socket.__spec__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('ModuleSpec')==True / socket.__spec__.name.__eq__('socket')==True / socket.__spec__.has_location==True / socket.__loader__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('SourceFileLoader')==True / type(socket.__spec__.origin).__name__.__eq__('str')==True — __spec__ is ModuleSpec; spec.name is 'socket'; has_location==True (loaded from socket.py); loader is SourceFileLoader (socket.py wraps _socket C extension); origin is str (path to socket.py); first sockmeta111 anchor"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: module_identity
  id_prefix: sockmeta111

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [spec_class_eq,   "socket.__spec__.__class__.__name__.__eq__",        ["ModuleSpec"],       true, "socket.__spec__.__class__.__name__ is 'ModuleSpec' (importlib.machinery.ModuleSpec; holds module metadata)"]
    - [spec_name_eq,    "socket.__spec__.name.__eq__",                      ["socket"],           true, "socket.__spec__.name is 'socket' (the fully qualified module name stored in the ModuleSpec)"]
    - [spec_has_loc,    "socket.__spec__.has_location",                     [],                   true, "socket.__spec__.has_location is True (module is loaded from socket.py on disk; not frozen or built-in)"]
    - [loader_class_eq, "socket.__loader__.__class__.__name__.__eq__",      ["SourceFileLoader"], true, "socket.__loader__.__class__.__name__ is 'SourceFileLoader' (socket.py is Python source wrapping _socket C extension)"]
    - [origin_type_str, "socket.__spec__.origin.__class__.__name__.__eq__", ["str"],              true, "type(socket.__spec__.origin) is 'str' (origin is the file path to socket.py as a string)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# len(socket.__all__) == 238
# socket.__all__[0].__eq__('fromfd')
# socket.__all__[-1].__eq__('recv_fds')
# socket.__package__.__eq__('')
# socket.__name__.__eq__('socket')
#
# Wave 271 theme: socket.__all__ length and boundary elements.
#
# socket.__all__ has 238 elements — much larger than hashlib.__all__ (19) because
# socket exports many constants (AF_*, SOCK_*, IPPROTO_*, SO_*, etc.) in addition
# to functions and classes. The first element is 'fromfd' and the last is 'recv_fds'.
# socket.__package__.__eq__('') confirms the empty string package (not None).
# socket.__name__.__eq__('socket') reconfirms the module name equality.
# No prior socket spec anchors socket.__all__ attributes.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table socket_extra111.socket_all_length_first_last_and_module_attrs:
  description: "socket.__all__.__len__()==238 / socket.__all__[0].__eq__('fromfd')==True / socket.__all__[-1].__eq__('recv_fds')==True / socket.__package__.__eq__('')==True / socket.__name__.__eq__('socket')==True — __all__ has 238 elements (far more than hashlib=19; socket exports many AF_*/SOCK_*/IPPROTO_* constants); first is 'fromfd'; last is 'recv_fds'; __package__ is '' (empty); __name__ is 'socket'; first sockmeta111 anchor"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: module_identity
  id_prefix: sockmeta111

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [all_len,         "socket.__all__.__len__",       [],           238,  "socket.__all__.__len__() is 238 (exports many constants: AF_*/SOCK_*/IPPROTO_*/SO_*/IP_*/TCP_* plus functions and classes)"]
    - [all_first_eq,    "socket.__all__[0].__eq__",     ["fromfd"],   true, "socket.__all__[0] is 'fromfd' (first exported name; creates socket from existing file descriptor)"]
    - [all_last_eq,     "socket.__all__[-1].__eq__",    ["recv_fds"], true, "socket.__all__[-1] is 'recv_fds' (last exported name; receives file descriptors from another process via ancillary data)"]
    - [package_eq2,     "socket.__package__.__eq__",    [""],         true, "socket.__package__.__eq__('') is True (empty string, not None; top-level module; len 0)"]
    - [name_eq2,        "socket.__name__.__eq__",       ["socket"],   true, "socket.__name__.__eq__('socket') is True (6 chars; module name; same string as socket.socket.__qualname__)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.__name__.__eq__('socket') — standalone
#
# socket.__name__ is 'socket'. The socket module __name__ attribute is 'socket'
# (6 chars: s-o-c-k-e-t). This is the module-level __name__, distinct from the
# class-level socket.socket.__qualname__ which is also 'socket'. Both the module
# and the class inside it share the same name 'socket' — this is a deliberate
# naming choice in Python's standard library (the socket module contains the
# socket class). socket_extra110 anchors socket.socket (class) module and qualname;
# this spec anchors the socket MODULE __name__ as a standalone under sockmeta111.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant socket_extra111.socket_module_name_eq:
  description: "socket.__name__.__eq__('socket') == True — module __name__ is 'socket' (6 chars; s-o-c-k-e-t); MODULE-level attribute (distinct from socket.socket CLASS __qualname__ which is also 'socket'); both module and class share same name 'socket'; extra110 anchors class attrs; first standalone for MODULE __name__ under sockmeta111"
  category: module_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "socket.__name__.__eq__"
  args: ["socket"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.__package__.__eq__('') — standalone
#
# socket.__package__ is '' (empty string). Like hashlib and uuid, socket is a
# top-level module with no parent package, so __package__ is '' (empty string,
# length 0). The empty string distinguishes top-level modules from submodules
# (like 'email.mime.text' which would have __package__=='email.mime') and from
# packages (which have __package__==__name__). socket.__package__ is '' not None
# — for source-loaded modules in Python 3, __package__ is always a string.
# No prior socket spec anchors socket MODULE __package__ equality as a standalone.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant socket_extra111.socket_module_package_eq_empty:
  description: "socket.__package__.__eq__('') == True — __package__ is '' (empty string, len 0); top-level module (no parent package); submodules have __package__ equal to parent package name; socket is a simple top-level module despite wrapping _socket; '' not None (source-loaded modules always have string __package__); no prior spec anchors as standalone; first standalone under sockmeta111"
  category: module_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "socket.__package__.__eq__"
  args: [""]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.__spec__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('ModuleSpec') — standalone
#
# socket.__spec__.__class__.__name__ is 'ModuleSpec'. ModuleSpec (from
# importlib.machinery) holds the metadata required to load a module: its name,
# loader, origin path, submodule_search_locations (for packages), and has_location
# flag. The ModuleSpec for socket is created by the path-based finder when it
# locates socket.py on sys.path. socket.__spec__ being a non-None ModuleSpec
# confirms socket is properly registered in the import system. This parallels
# hashlib.__spec__ (also ModuleSpec) and uuid.__spec__ (also ModuleSpec).
# No prior socket spec anchors socket MODULE __spec__ class name as a standalone.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant socket_extra111.socket_module_spec_is_modulespec:
  description: "socket.__spec__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('ModuleSpec') == True — MODULE-level __spec__ is a ModuleSpec (importlib.machinery.ModuleSpec; holds name, loader, origin, has_location); created by path-based finder when locating socket.py; non-None __spec__ confirms proper import system registration; parallels hashlib.__spec__ and uuid.__spec__ (both ModuleSpec); no prior spec anchors as standalone; first standalone under sockmeta111"
  category: module_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "socket.__spec__.__class__.__name__.__eq__"
  args: ["ModuleSpec"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.__spec__.has_location == True — standalone
#
# socket.__spec__.has_location is True. The socket module is implemented as
# socket.py (Python source file) — a wrapper around the _socket C extension.
# has_location True means socket has a concrete file path on disk (the origin
# is the path to socket.py). This confirms socket is loaded from a .py file
# using SourceFileLoader, not from a frozen module or built-in. The _socket
# C extension (which provides the low-level socket functionality) would have
# a different module spec — ExtensionFileLoader and a .so/.dylib origin.
# No prior socket spec anchors socket MODULE __spec__.has_location as a standalone.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant socket_extra111.socket_module_spec_has_location:
  description: "socket.__spec__.has_location == True — has_location is True; socket is implemented as socket.py (.py source file wrapping _socket C extension); has concrete file path on disk (origin is path to socket.py); loaded by SourceFileLoader; _socket C extension has different spec (ExtensionFileLoader); no prior spec anchors as standalone; first standalone under sockmeta111"
  category: module_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "socket.__spec__.has_location"
  args: []
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.__loader__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('SourceFileLoader') — standalone
#
# socket.__loader__.__class__.__name__ is 'SourceFileLoader'. SourceFileLoader
# (from importlib._bootstrap_external) is used to load Python .py source files.
# socket.py is the Python-level wrapper for the _socket C extension that provides
# the actual networking functionality. The fact that socket uses SourceFileLoader
# parallels hashlib (also SourceFileLoader wrapping _hashlib). Both are pure-Python
# wrapper modules that import from a C extension to do the heavy lifting.
# socket_extra110 anchors socket.socket class __module__ equality; this spec
# anchors socket MODULE __loader__ type as a standalone under sockmeta111.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant socket_extra111.socket_module_loader_is_sourcefileloader:
  description: "socket.__loader__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('SourceFileLoader') == True — loader is SourceFileLoader (importlib._bootstrap_external; loads .py source files); socket.py is Python wrapper around _socket C extension; parallels hashlib (also SourceFileLoader wrapping _hashlib); both are pure-Python modules that delegate to C extensions; no prior spec anchors as standalone; first standalone under sockmeta111"
  category: module_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "socket.__loader__.__class__.__name__.__eq__"
  args: ["SourceFileLoader"]
  expected: true
